step_data.thought: Now I'm on the Groups dashboard page. Looking at the accessibility tree, I can see there are groups listed, including 'Test Group' and 'Development Team'. However, I don't see any explicit indication that these groups have subgroups or a way to expand them directly from this view. In GitLab, to view a group's hierarchy and its subgroups, I typically need to navigate to the group's page first. From there, I can see and expand the subgroup hierarchy. Let me click on one of the groups, such as 'Test Group', to navigate to its page where I should be able to see if it has any subgroups and expand them.
